	"cache_media_name": "Media Cache",
	"cache_media_desc": "Disk-based cache for audio files (songs, podcasts, radio segments).",
	"cache_media_how_1": "Audio files are cached on disk after first playback, so repeated listens don't re-fetch from the backend. This dramatically reduces bandwidth and improves response time.",
	"cache_media_how_2": "The cache uses the same sharded SHA-256 directory structure as the image cache. Files are stored with their original content type (audio/mpeg, audio/flac, audio/ogg, etc.).",
	"cache_media_how_3": "Default limit is 2 GB with a 30-day TTL. Oldest files are evicted first when the cache is full.",
	"cache_media_how_4": "All three settings can be overridden via environment variables: MEDIA_CACHE_DIR, MEDIA_CACHE_MAX_SIZE_MB, MEDIA_CACHE_TTL_DAYS. When set, the corresponding UI field is locked.",
	"cache_media_how_5": "This cache is especially useful for Electron builds where offline playback and reduced network usage are important.",
	"cache_image_name": "Image Cache",
	"cache_image_desc": "Disk-based cache for album art, radio favicons, and podcast artwork.",
	"cache_image_how_1": "All images (album art, radio favicons, podcast artwork) are fetched through a server-side cache proxy. On first load, images are downloaded from the origin and stored on disk. Subsequent requests serve from cache.",
	"cache_image_how_2": "Cached files are organized in sharded subdirectories using SHA-256 hashes. When the cache exceeds the maximum size, the oldest entries are evicted first.",
	"cache_image_how_3": "Each backend uses a compound protocol prefix (e.g. demo-image://, radiobrowser-image://) so the cache can route requests to the correct origin with appropriate authentication headers when needed.",
	"cache_image_how_4": "All three settings can be overridden via environment variables: IMAGE_CACHE_DIR, IMAGE_CACHE_MAX_SIZE_MB, IMAGE_CACHE_TTL_DAYS. When set, the corresponding UI field is locked.",
	"cache_metadata_name": "Metadata Cache",
	"cache_metadata_desc": "In-memory cache for radio stream now-playing info and other transient metadata.",
	"cache_metadata_how_1": "When listening to internet radio, ICY metadata (artist and track name) is extracted from the audio stream headers and cached in memory.",
